        <h1>LeetCode 1018: Binary Prefix Divisible By 5 (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a binary array nums (0-indexed). We interpret i-th binary prefix from nums as a number
                from
                the most significant bit to the least significant bit. For example, if nums = [1,0,1], the 0-th prefix
                is
                1, the 1-st prefix is 10 (binary for 2), and the 2-nd prefix is 101 (binary for 5). Return an array of
                booleans answer where answer[i] is true if the i-th prefix is divisible by 5, and false otherwise.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [0,1,1] → Output: [true,false,false]. The prefixes are 0, 01 (1), and 011 (3). Only 0 is
                divisible by 5.
                Input: nums = [1,1,1] → Output: [false,false,false]. The prefixes are 1, 11 (3), and 111 (7). None are
                divisible by 5.
                Input: nums = [0,1,1,1,1,1] → Output: [true,false,false,false,true,false]. Prefixes: 0 (divisible), 1,
                3,
                7, 15 (divisible), 31.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    vector&lt;bool&gt; prefixesDivBy5(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; a) {
        vector&lt;bool&gt; res;
        int x = 0; // running value mod 5
        for (int b : a) {
            x = (x * 2 + b) % 5;     // update prefix mod 5
            res.push_back(x == 0);   // divisible if mod == 0
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
